<HEADER>
A5922 &Cx1f; var-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-R-BIBLE-BOOKS-REVIEW-     04-05 1072
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-R-BIBLE-BOOKS-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THERE'S THE GOOD BOOK, AND THEN THERE ARE ALL OF THESE BOOKS 
</HEADLINE>
  
(Repeating for all needing.)  (The Week in Review)  
 (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   If someone in Afghanistan were to title a cookbook ``The Koran
of Barbecue,'' it's a fair bet that the mullahs would show their
appreciation by employing its wisdom to roast the author himself on
the spit.
</P>
<P>
   Yet things are different in America. Here the sacred and the
secular have mixed readily to bring forth biblical film
blockbusters featuring bad 1950s hairdos.
</P>
<P>
   And in that tradition, the publishing industry _ no stranger to
overstatement _ has for a long time been cranking out multitudes of
``bibles.'' Behold, an Easter assortment!
</P>
<P>
   _ By TOM KUNTZ
</P>
<P>
   THE ARCHER'S AND BOWHUNTER'S BIBLE (Doubleday Outdoor Bibles,
1993) by H. Lea Lawrence
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``The display of dead animals isn't appreciated by
the public nor, for that matter, by most hunters.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``In many ways, the wily coyote could be classed as
the king of the varmints. It is intelligent, crafty, fast, rough
and, best of all from a varmint hunter's standpoint, numerous.''
</P>
<P>
   THE BARBECUE! BIBLE (Workman, 1998) by Steven Raichlen
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Cleanliness may be next to godliness when it
comes to personal hygiene, but don't overdo it when it comes to
your grill.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: Beer Can Chicken! ``This odd recipe makes some of
the most moist, succulent, flavorful barbecued chicken I've ever
tasted. The secret: an open can of beer is inserted into the cavity
of the bird. . . .''
</P>
<P>
   THE BARTENDER'S BIBLE (Harper Collins, 1991) by Gary Regan
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Be forewarned. . . . There will always be someone
who wants a liqueur you don't have. You know, the one he drank on a
riverboat on the Ganges back in 1927; it tasted a little like
kirsch, except that it reminded him of cornflakes with sliced
bananas at the time.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``Within the book, drinks are listed alphabetically
under the predominant liquor in that drink. A Harvey Wallbanger is
listed under Vodka.''
</P>
<P>
   THE CHEESE BIBLE (Penguin Studio, 1998) by Christian Teubner
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Tilsit and other semi-hard loaf-shaped cheeses
are cut into slices with a two-handled knife.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation (from the jacket blurb): ``The title of this book is
no idle boast, for it is  &UR; the &LR;  most complete and most beautifully
illustrated reference work on one of mankind's most popular foods.
The first chapter tells us exactly what cheese is and discusses the
methods of its production. The next chapter is a comprehensive
encyclopedia of cheeses from all around the world. After telling
the readers about Cheese in the Kitchen, the remainder of this
gorgeous book is devoted to the many imaginative ways that cheese
can be used.''
</P>
<P>
   THE CHOCOLATE BIBLE (Penguin Studio, 1997) by Christian Teubner
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Macaroons and chocolate go together well.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation (from the jacket blurb): ``The title of this book is
no idle boast, for it is  &UR; the &LR;  most complete and most beautifully
illustrated reference work ever to be published on one of mankind's
most delectable foods. . . .''
</P>
<P>
   THE HOME DECORATOR'S BIBLE (Crown, 1996)
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Clean off any paint that drips onto woodwork
immediately. It is easier to remove when it is still wet.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``Color in particular is so much a part of our lives
that we often take it for granted _ until such time as we are
deprived of it. Not so long ago, visitors to the former Soviet
Union invariably remarked on how colorless the cities there seemed,
thanks to the absence of any street advertising.''
</P>
<P>
   THE BIBLE OF KARATE: BUBISHI (Charles E. Tuttle, 1995)
translated with commentary by Patrick McCarthy
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``If attacked from the front, consider attacking
the groin.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``The Claw Hand is an effective technique and is
especially effective for dislocating the jaw. . . . Medical
treatment must be quickly rendered if struck with the Claw Hand. If
not, internal hemorrhaging will be followed by three days of
vomiting blood, and death within one month.''
</P>
<P>
   THE PIE AND PASTRY BIBLE (Scribner, 1998) by Rose Levy
Beranbaum, also author of ``The Cake Bible''
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``The more you make dough, the better you get.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``Many people think of me as `the cake lady,' but
the truth is I am more a pastry person!''
</P>
<P>
   THE ROSE BIBLE (Chronicle Books, 1998) by Rayford Clayton
Reddell
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Pruning rules are made to be broken, such as the
number of canes left on a well-pruned bush.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelations:`` `President Herbert Hoover' is an eternally
popular bicolor. . . . `Sexy Rexy,' as its name would imply, has
proved to be a virile stud in current hybridizing trends.''
</P>
<P>
   THE SHOOTER'S BIBLE (Stoeger Publishing, 1998)
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``Ruffed grouse that offer hard and fast crossing
shots are invariably ahead of the muzzle, which means you must come
from behind and swing through the target.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation (from an advertisement): ``The name Smith &AMP; Wesson
has long been associated with fine quality handguns. . . . Smith &AMP;
Wesson hip flasks proudly pay tribute to that fine name with
embossed Smith &AMP; Wesson logos.''
</P>
<P>
   THE WINDOWS 98 BIBLE (Peachpit Press, 1998) by Fred Davis and
Kip Crosby
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``If your Start Menu is getting gnarly, you don't
need to delete superfluous items through Taskbar Properties. Just
navigate to the item you want to prune, right-click it and pick
Delete.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: ``Unlike DriveSpace, which plays tricks with
compression and slack space, FAT32 installs an entirely new _ and
significantly more space efficient _ filesystem that radically
decreases cluster size. By doing so, it alleviates the most
wasteful aspect of FAT16 and brings the FAT filesystem into sync
with the modern world of multi-gigabyte drives.''
</P>
<P>
   EARL MINDELL'S VITAMIN BIBLE (Warner Books, 1991)
</P>
<P>
   Commandment: ``If you're unsure as to whether you'd be better
off with a powder, a liquid, or a tablet, regular vitamin E or dry,
taking supplements three times a day or time released, my advice to
you is to experiment.''
</P>
<P>
   Revelation: `` `Spanish fly' is actually `cantharides' made from
the outer skeletons of beetles. It causes itching, but not
necessarily for sex.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
