<P>
   &UR; NUCLEAR FUSION POSSIBLE ON A TABLETOP &LR;  _ Nuclear fusion can now
be carried out on a tabletop, making it possible to study the
process at a fraction of the usual cost. Physicists in California
have triggered fusion using a small laser which has highly
concentrated energy capable of fusing atoms. By Charles Seife.
1,800 words. (slugged: BC-NUCLEAR-FUSION-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE WATER FALLING FROM OUR SKIES IS UNFIT TO DRINK &LR;  _ A new
study from Switzerland reveals that much of the rain in Europe is
laced with toxic pesticides at levels so high that it would be
illegal to supply it as drinking water. Meanwhile, Swedish
researchers have linked pesticides to one of the most rapidly
increasing cancers in the Western world. By Fred Pearce and Debora
MacKenzie. 600 words. (slugged:
BC-IT'S-RAINING-PESTICIDES-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TRADITIONAL PLANT BREEDING CAN PRODUCE A SUPERIOR FRUIT &LR;  _
Strawberries could soon become tastier thanks to the British
discovery of the genes which govern the flavor of strawberries and
make them red. And given the current furor over genetic
modification of crops, the researchers hope to develop superior
strawberries by using traditional plant-breeding methods. By Andy
Coghlan. 600 words. (slugged:
BC-SWEETER-STRAWBERRIES-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DANGEROUS BUGS MAY BE LURKING IN YOUR PIPES &LR;  _ A bacterium that
causes a variety of gastrointestinal diseases, from ulcers to
cancer, could be lurking in our water pipes. Researchers from
Aberdeen found that the slime that coats the inside of water pipes
can provide a haven for Helicobacter pylori, even if the water is
chlorinated. However, water companies say there are no studies that
show H. pylori in treated water. By Jon Copley. 500 words.
(slugged: BC-ULCERS-ON-TAP-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL;
</P>
