<SLUG> BC-SALTER-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WHITHER COMPASSION? 
</HEADLINE>
   Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By STEPHANIE SALTER  
 c.1999 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ ``As you are, so is the world'' _ Ramana
Maharshi
</P>
<P>
   Can you believe those Serbs over in Kosovo? Killing and
torturing people who look just like them because of something that
happened in 1389?
</P>
<P>
   What's the matter with those people? Do they thrive on bloodshed
and violence? It makes you wonder sometimes if they're actually
human.
</P>
<P>
   ``I am part and parcel of the whole and cannot find God apart
from the rest of humanity.'' _ Mahatma Gandhi
</P>
<P>
   What a surprise _ the peace talks in Northern Ireland have
stalled. One side has demanded the other first turn over its
weapons. Fat chance.
</P>
<P>
   Those people have been fighting each other for hundreds of
years. ``The Troubles'' is their way of life. They instinctively
objectify one another. They'll never have peace. They don't really
want it.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Returning violence for violence multiplies violence, adding
deeper darkness to a night already devoid of stars. Darkness cannot
drive out darkness; only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out
hate; only love can do that.'' _ Martin Luther King Jr.
</P>
<P>
   How about those Hutus and Tutsis in Rwanda? Life isn't hard
enough for those people? They're not poor enough, they don't have
enough famines, floods and droughts? No, one side has to hack the
other side to death with machetes. They must be nuts.
</P>
<P>
   At least they aren't cannibalizing one another, which is what
those people in Indonesia are doing. What in heaven's name could
possess them? To eat another person _ not because you're starving
but as a political statement _ you'd have to convince yourself they
weren't even human.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``O God, help us not to despise or oppose what we do not
understand.'' _ William Penn
</P>
<P>
   What is it with these homosexuals anyway? Why do they have to
hold hands and kiss in public? Why do they keep trying to get
special laws passed just for them? Why in the world should they be
allowed to get married, let alone adopt children?
</P>
<P>
   It's bad enough that those people are the way they are, but then
they have to advertise it. No wonder they get beat up. They make
normal people want to vomit.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't ever let them pull you down so low as to hate them.'' _
Booker T. Washington
</P>
<P>
   Somebody really must stop those radical right-wing Christians.
</P>
<P>
   Always sticking their noses into other people's bedrooms, trying
to tell women what to do with their own bodies. They and their
boycotts of Disney. Those people are sick, sick, sick.
</P>
<P>
   They talk about God all the time, but they just sow hatred and
anger. They're Nazis. They don't know what the word ``love'' means.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Any persons you have ever met, even if you have just exchanged
a glance on a bus, have become a part of your being, and
consequently you are in some sense ultimately responsible for them.
You carry them in your heart.'' _ Swami Venkatesananda
</P>
<P>
   Can you believe the way people drive these days? Everybody's out
for himself. They cut you off, sneak in line, tailgate and drive
too fast.
</P>
<P>
   Nobody uses turn signals, but everybody sure uses their horn.
</P>
<P>
   They're like animals behind the wheel, those people. They act
like they're the only ones on the road, the only ones in a hurry.
It makes you want to scream _ or ram right into their stupid cars.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``While you are proclaiming peace with your lips, be careful to
have it in your heart.'' _ St. Francis of Assisi
</P>
<P>
   Sometimes it's hard not to feel like you're the last decent
person on Earth. The way kids dress these days with their pants
down around their knees, the way they use such foul language on the
bus. What planet are they from? Nobody has manners anymore.
</P>
<P>
   Everybody's a smartass.
</P>
<P>
   Then there are ``the homeless.'' Those people live like pigs.
</P>
<P>
   They sleep on the sidewalk, pee in public, throw trash on the
ground and do nothing all day but beg for money. Why should anybody
feel sorry for them? They choose to live the way they do.
</P>
<P>
   What we need is a big old bulldozer to scrape them up and take
them to the dump with the rest of the garbage.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``In separateness lies the world's great misery; in compassion
lies the world's true strength.'' _ Buddha
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Stephanie Salter is a columnist for the San Francisco Examiner,
P.O. Box 7260, San Francisco, CA 94120. Her e-mail address is
salter &LR; examiner.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
