<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   US-KOSOVO (Washington) _ By ordering Apache anti-tank
helicopters and long-range rocket launchers to Albania, President
Clinton lays the groundwork for an allied-enforced sanctuary inside
Kosovo to protect 65,000 ethnic Albanians backed up on the
Macedonian border. Clinton updates the nation at 2:15 p.m. EDT as
the United States and other nations offer temporary sanctuary for
refugees. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   COURT-SEARCH (Washington) _ The Supreme Court significantly
expands the power of police to search motor vehicles, ruling that
officers can look through the belongings of all passengers inside a
car when lawfully seeking criminal evidence against the driver. By
MARK HELM.
</P>
