</P>
<P>
   Ballmer's verbal outbursts have also hurt his company's
reputation. Shortly after the Department of Justice began its
latest battle with Microsoft in October 1997, he bellowed at
reporters: ``To heck with (Attorney-General) Janet Reno.'' A few
weeks later at a trade show, he screamed ``What the consumer needs
is more, more, more Windows.''
</P>
<P>
   He says he regrets those comments, and wants to ``stop saying
stupid things.''
</P>
<P>
   But when this big, balding man starts gesticulating wildly to
make a point, one minute a tyrant, the next a little boy, you
