that same company admitted that last year, it wrote checks for
billions of dollars in improper payments, had only a rough estimate
of its loans, and lacked adequate records for a majority of its
buildings, facilities and equipment. That is the financial
condition of the U.S. government and its 24 major separtments and
agencies, according to the 1998 financial audit released quietly
last week. (Malone, Cox News Service).
