<HEADLINE>
EDGY ANIMATION COMES TO DVD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVID BLOOM  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ If living and viewing in ``Pleasantville'' isn't
quite your DVD style, try the just-released ``General Chaos
Uncensored Animation'' disc from Manga Video.
</P>
<P>
   There's a lot of great stuff on the disc, some 40 animated
shorts from around the world, but be warned that it's not for the
delicate and sensitive. As the box warns, it has ``plenty of sex,
tons of violence and enough subversive humor for even the most
twisted mind.''
</P>
<P>
   Among the best-known contributors are Bill Plympton and the
bolexbrothers' Mike Booth, as well as contributors to shows such as
``Beavis &AMP; Butt-head,'' ``Rocko's Modern Life'' and ``Daria,''
among many others.
</P>
<P>
   Given the nature of the disc, it probably won't be in your local
Blockbuster. Go to www.manga.com for ordering info.
</P>
</TEXT>
