</P>
<P>
   GA-INDUS-TRADE _ ATLANTA _ Georgia Gov. Roy Barnes is expected
to name a new Industry and Trade board chairman today, probably
R.K. Sehgal. (Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PERSONAL TECHNOLOGY PAGE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0402 _ Headsets traditionally have been associated
with switchboard operators, workers who spend their entire days
making phone connections. More recently, headset use has spread to
other office workers who need to type, take notes or shuffle papers
while talking on the phone. Now the big push is toward headsets at
home. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) Art includes 4-column color
photo of woman working while wearing a headset.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ALPHA KEYBOARD _ Anyone who has ever carried around a laptop
computer knows even the lightest machine becomes a heavyweight over
time. So it was with some concern that I began searching for
portable options for my son to use for writing at home and school.
While cruising Web sites about technology and learning, I
discovered the AlphaSmart keyboard. I'm glad I did. (Hill, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes 1-column B&AMP;W photo of the
keyboard.
</P>
<P>
   TECH NOTES _ Everyone knows the best use of the Web isn't
research, nor is it finding out if it's going to rain tomorrow. The
most important use of the Web is getting your horoscope. Otherwise,
why would there be so many different horoscope sites on the Web?
(Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 2-column color
photo of web site.
</P>
<P>
   TECHNOBUDDY _ In honor of spring, we'll do some computer
cleaning that could save you money and will surely make your
machine last longer. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.) Art
includes 1 column color sig of columnist.
</P>
