<P>
   COXNET PTECH 0402 _ Headsets traditionally have been associated
with switchboard operators, workers who spend their entire days
making phone connections. More recently, headset use has spread to
other office workers who need to type, take notes or shuffle papers
while talking on the phone. Now the big push is toward headsets at
home. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) Art includes 4-column color
photo of woman working while wearing a headset.
