   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S `THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``According to the New York Times, when Hillary got home from
her trip to Africa, she and President Clinton allegedly made
passionate love on the floor inside the front of the White House.
April Fools!''
</P>
<P>
   ``Monica Lewinsky, currently in France now on her book tour. If
I'm not mistaken, I believe French is her native tongue.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Scientists say that your nose and ears will keep growing over
the course of your lifetime. If that's the case, Evander Holyfield
might want to fight Tyson again just to get a trim.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A new study says that married people weigh more than unmarried
people. Well you know guys are gonna jump all over this study.
`Honey, of course I wanna marry you, but you don't wanna gain
weight.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Some sad news. Roseanne's ex-husband Tom Arnold, divorcing his
second wife after just three and a half years of marriage. Arnold
said today that no matter how long he stuck with this marriage,
there was simply no chance she was gonna get her own sitcom.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Our good friend Cindy Crawford says she lost five pounds in
the first three months of her pregnancy because she got morning
sickness and she kept throwing up. Course, when you're a supermodel
with morning sickness, you're throwing up for two.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Big news from the campaign trail. While campaigning in New
Hampshire yesterday, Al Gore took off his suit jacket and tie. This
was a shock to his wife Tipper. He doesn't even do that during sex.
I think he unbuttons it for a second.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The movie ``The Mod Squad'' opened over the weekend. About an
African American man, a rich kid, and a woman, who come together as
police officers to fight crime. I understand Dennis Rodman was up
for all three parts.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to a new book, they asked 50 women what they would
do if they had a male sex organ for one day. Most of them said,
`Probably get a salary increase.'''
