___
</P>
<P>
   ``In 1997, (basketball star) Michael Jordan visited Wrigley
Field, and Cubs officials went to his skybox to ask him if he
wanted to come up to the (WGN) booth and spend a few minutes with
Harry, who absolutely adored Michael.
</P>
<P>
   ```No way,' Michael said. `I can't do it.'
</P>
<P>
   ```Why not?' '' asked a befuddled Cubs official.
</P>
<P>
   ```I love Harry,' Michael said, `but I don't want to go on the
air and have him introduce me as Michael Jackson.' ''
_ from Where's Harry,? by Steve Stone with Barry Rozner.
</P>
