<HEADER>
A6808 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      04-05 0549
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release TUESDAY AMs, April 6, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ATROCITIES (Washington) _ Pentagon says the military has
its first clear satellite images of atrocities against ethnic
Albanians, leaving President Clinton to defend a seemingly futile
bombing campaign against Yugoslavia. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1350
words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CLINTON (Washington) _ President Clinton, vowing that
ethnic Albanians will return to Kosovo, says the ethnic cleansing
by Serb forces ``cannot stand.'' By Ann Scales. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEES-HEALTH (Blace, Macedonia) -- More than 50,000 refugees
stranded in an open field on the Kosovo border will begin to die in
large numbers if they are not moved in the next few days, medical
authorities say. By Kevin Cullen. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RELOCATE (Washington) _ Relocating Kosovar Albanians to
Guam and Guantanamo would be no small cultural and climactic shock.
Immigration laws, and US facilities that are on US possessions but
not in the United States proper, are the controlling factors. By
Mary Leonard. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LIBYA-PANAM (New York) _ Clearing the way for justice after more
than a decade of defiance, Libya hands over two suspects in the
1988 Pan Am jet bombing. UN promptly suspends sanctions against
Libya. By Colum Lynch. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCI-ANGIOGENESIS (Undated) _ Angiogenesis inhibitors _ drugs
hailed as opening a new era in cancer treatment _ can also retard
artery-blocking deposits that cause heart attacks and strokes. By
Richard Saltus. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   ELDERLY-DRINKING (Undated) _ One-third of all the elderly -- and
three-quarters of those who drink -- drink too much. Ten percent of
elderly drinkers are doing it on a binge basis. By Larry Tye. 800
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE-TRADING (Undated) _ Investors funneled stock trades
through the Internet at a record pace in the first quarter; online
trading volumes rose 30 to 35 percent from the fourth quarter. By
Steven Wilmsen. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   HANCOCK-CHINA (Boston) _ John Hancock wins permission from the
government to sell life insurance in China. By Lynnley Browning.
600 words.
</P>
<P>
