<HEADLINE>
CLIPPERS' TAYLOR HURTING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ This is not the balanced attack the Clippers had
expected from Maurice Taylor.
</P>
<P>
   No, they had expected points AND rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, the only balance the power forward - who leads the team
in scoring, but missed-rebound opportunities -- has provided in
recent days is strain in each Achilles tendon.
</P>
<P>
   ``Both sides are tight,'' said Taylor, who didn't play in
Sunday's loss at Denver, but will attempt to perform in tonight's
game with Phoenix at the Sports Arena. ``They've been bothering me
a while. At first, I just thought it was from playing so many
games, but this has been going on too long.''
</P>
<P>
   Lorenzen Wright started in Taylor's place at Denver, and his 11
rebounds helped the Clippers overcome Danny Forston and Antonio
McDyess to win the backboard rumble, 42-40.
</P>
<P>
   The scoring, of course, was won by the Nuggets.
</P>
<P>
   Sunday's defeat was the Clippers' 29th in 32 games, bad enough
for a winning percentage of .094. The worst percentage in league
history was the .110 turned in by the 1972-'73 Philadelphia 76ers.
</P>
<P>
   Subhead Making another point
</P>
<P>
   Veteran playmaker Sherman Douglas scored 10 points, handed out
six assists and committed one turnover against Denver in his second
appearance since returning from the injured list.
</P>
<P>
   Douglas, whose injured groin invited a subsequent thigh injury,
said his push for optimum fitness is ``about 90 percent.''
</P>
<P>
   He played 27 minutes vs. the Nuggets, with starter Darrick
Martin logging 18 and Troy Hudson - on his second, 10-day contract
after escaping from the CBA - on the court for only six.
</P>
<P>
   All three could be called upon to chase the Suns' Jason Kidd
tonight.
</P>
<P>
   ``Someone has to do it,'' said Douglas, who signed a one-year
contract the day before the Clippers opened the season against
Phoenix. ``I'm more ready now than I've been since I got here.''
</P>
</TEXT>
