<SLUG> BC-MOSAIX-LUCENT-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LUCENT TECHNOLOGIES AGREES TO BY MOSAIZ INC.  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ARTHUR C.GORLICK  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ Lucent Technologies Inc., the world's largest
telecommunications equipment maker, said Monday it agreed to buy
Redmond, Wash.-based Mosaix Inc., which provides customer service
management software, for $145 million in stock,
</P>
<P>
   Mosaix has a staff of about 550 employees, including 300 in
Redmond, 100 in Alameda, Calif., about 60 in the United Kingdom and
the remainder scattered throughout the world, said spokesman Darren
Storedahl.
</P>
<P>
   No layoffs or relocations are anticipated, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The acquisition will allow Lucent to expand in the fast-growing
area of ``customer relationship management'' and to increase its
portfolio of products that cater to companies using telephone
customer service representatives.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are a leader in customer care solutions and technology and
we were looking for a partner to round out our products and
expertise,'' said Janice Anderson, Lucent's vice president for
customer care solutions.
</P>
<P>
   Mosaix's software creates a record of customer transactions,
preferences and buying patterns. Its list of business customers
includes some of the world's top telecomunications, banking,
financial and insurance companies.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are also other sectors, and retail is one of them ...
looking for customer relationship management solutions, so that
probably will be an area that will be most active,'' said Nicholas
Tiliacos, Mosaix president and chief executive officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lucent has complementary products to our own, worldwide
positioning and reach ... and partnering with a company like Lucent
will allow us to access that all the better.''
</P>
<P>
   Mosaix's software, called ViewStar, allows companies to
stimulate business by indentifying customers' buying patterns and
then marketing products that match customer needs and preferences.
</P>
<P>
   Mosaix's customer relationship management software automates and
streamlines information about customer requests and the tasks
required to fullfill them, allowing companies to manage work
related to customer requests.
</P>
<P>
   Lucent, a telecommunications and software giant based in Murray
Hill, N.J., has about 120,000 employees. It researches, designs,
develops and manufactures communications systems, software and
products, including telephone systems, through Bell Laboratories.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're still developing a structural plan but we consider this
acquisition by Lucent to be a real positive for the company and the
people here who have said, `I wish I had the backing and resources
to do what I want,''' Mosaix's Storedahl said.``Working with a
company like Lucent just opens doors for those people.''
</P>
<P>
   Under terms of the merger agreement, each share of Mosaix will
be converted into 0.1927 shares of Lucent _ $10.77 per Mosaix
share, based on Lucent's April 1 close of $55.875.
</P>
<P>
   The exchange rate reflects the two-for-one split of Lucent's
stock effective April 1.
</P>
<P>
   The merger, expected to be completed in the quarter ending June
30, is subject to the approval of Mosaix shareholders and other
customary conditions. Mosaix has not determined whether the
proposed issue of about 2.8 million shares will be made through a
public offering or a private placement.
</P>
<P>
   Lucent closed yesterday at 58 15/16, up 3 1/16. Mosaix closed at
10 3/4, up 2 3/8.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
