<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, APRIL 6
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-KLA-NYT (moved on Saturday, Apr. 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, Apr. 3,
about the history of conflict between Serbs and Albanians
misspelled the surname of the contemporary British historian who
observed that no lands have ``suffered more from the whims of
international politics'' than the Balkans. He is Norman Davies, not
Davis.
</P>
<P>
   The article also misspelled the surname of the dictator who
ruled Albania from 1945 to 1985. He was Enver Hoxha, not Hoxa.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INDIA-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Apr. 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 4,
about a dispute that threatens to topple India's coalition
Government misidentified the Cabinet post of George Fernandes,
whose dismissal has been demanded by Jayalalitha Jayaram, leader of
one party in the coalition. Mr. Fernandes is the Defense Minister,
not the Defense Secretary.
</P>
<P>
   BC-RATES-NYT (moved on Thursday, Apr. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent Thursday, Apr. 1,
about the recent increase in mortgage rates misstated the minimum
size of mortgages classified as large. It is $240,000, not
$227,150.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Mar. 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Mar.
31, about computer viruses, misstated the availability of free
on-line updates for the Mc-Afee Virus Scan software program from
McAfee, a division of Network Associates. The updates are available
indefinitely, not just for a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
