adventurous new playwrights and actors to the American stage earned
her the title Queen of Off Broadway, died Sunday at New York
Presbyterian Hospital in Manhattan. She was 98 and had homes in
Manhattan and Westport. (Suzanne DeChillo/New York Times Photo)
