cuneiform, at a symposium on the origins or writing held at the
University of Pennsylvania. ``Whatever the mutual influences of
writing systems of different cultures may be, their great variety
shows, at least, that the development of writing, once it is
initiated, attains a considerable degree of independence and
flexibility,'' he says. (Sal DiMarco Jr./New York Times Photo)
</P>
